data.description: The quiet neighborhood welcomes you to this house that has been the owners' pride & joy. The front of the house is immaculate, with a beautiful lawn large enough for yard games galore. The front yard also features the first of TWO large natural gas fire pits on the property, to enjoy those chilly evenings with family and friends. Upon entering the home, you are greeted with vaulted ceilings & an open, welcoming layout. To your right, enter the spacious living room & enjoy views of Pikes Peak while you cozy up on the front window seat. The kitchen features custom cherry wood cabinetry, under-cabinet lighting, and plenty of space for cooking & entertaining. Off the kitchen, step out onto the balcony to sip your morning coffee. Heading upstairs, the large master bedroom is bright and open with vaulted ceilings and a master bathroom attached. There are two more bedrooms and one full bathroom upstairs. Both upstairs bathrooms are updated & complete with newer Velux skylights for plenty of natural lighting. Heading down to the lower level, the entertaining possibilities continue. Currently being used as a media/movie room, this room features a wood-burning fireplace & is also viewable from the kitchen upstairs, giving an open feel when entertaining guests on multiple levels. Walk out the French doors and escape to the private backyard complete with a large, lighted cedar gazebo, perfect for mounting a TV and watching your favorite sports games. A second gas fire pit next to the gazebo provides the warmth for the evening while you enjoy the views of Pulpit Rock! The backyard also includes a trampoline & natural gas connections for a BBQ/grill. Back in the house, a garden level basement features plenty of natural light, another family room, two nice-sized bedrooms, bathroom, & a laundry room. Other features: trailer/boat storage on side of the house, ceiling fans in all bedrooms. New in 2019: Roof, gutters, exterior paint, water heater, & central a/c.
